# Hoist OpenTelemetry runtime-patching shims to the workspace root node_modules
# so Next.js can resolve them as serverExternalPackages from apps/web.
#
# @sentry/nextjs pulls in @opentelemetry/instrumentation, which depends on
# require-in-the-middle (CJS) and import-in-the-middle (ESM). Under pnpm these
# live only in the nested .pnpm store, so Next's bundler warns:
#   "Package require-in-the-middle can't be external ... could not be resolved
#    by Node.js from the project directory."
# public-hoist-pattern appends to pnpm's defaults (*eslint*, *prettier*) and
# surfaces these at app/node_modules, where apps/web resolves them.
#
# Takes effect on the next `pnpm install` (run from app/).
public-hoist-pattern[]=*require-in-the-middle*
public-hoist-pattern[]=*import-in-the-middle*

# NOTE: applying these hoist patterns requires `pnpm install` (run from app/),
# which pnpm 10 does as a full node_modules purge + rebuild. Run it in a real
# terminal (it prompts Y/n) when no dev server / other session is using the
# tree. Until then the benign "require-in-the-middle can't be external" dev
# warning persists — it has no runtime effect (Sentry is DSN-gated, off in dev).
